<div class="cookie-container mt-10 px-8">
  <h1 id="title" class="text-center font-semibold text-lg">Cookie Policy</h1>
  <p class="privacy-details text-sm/6 text-gray-900 mt-2"><strong class="font-semibold">Effective Date:</strong> April 15, 2024</p>
  <p class="privacy-details text-sm/6 text-gray-900"><strong class="font-semibold">Last Updated:</strong> April 24, 2026</p>

  <p class="cookie-details mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-700">
    This Cookie Policy explains how we use browser cookies and similar technologies to operate, secure, and improve our platform. It also describes your choices regarding the use of non‑essential cookies. This policy should be read together with our Privacy Policy, which outlines how we process personal data.
  </p>

  <p class="cookie-details mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-700">
    By continuing to use our website or platform, you acknowledge the use of cookies as described in this policy.
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">1. What Are Cookies</h2>
  <p class="cookie-details mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-700">
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser. They allow us to maintain secure sessions, remember user preferences, improve platform performance, analyze usage patterns, and deliver a consistent and reliable experience. Cookies may be set directly by us (“first‑party cookies”) or by third‑party providers (“third‑party cookies”).
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

  <h3 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">2.1 Essential Cookies (Required)</h3>
  <p class="cookie-details mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-700">
    These cookies are necessary for the platform to function and cannot be disabled. They support authentication, secure login, session management, load balancing, and core platform features. Without these cookies, the service cannot be delivered reliably.
  </p>

  <h3 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">2.2 Functional Cookies (Optional)</h3>
  <p class="cookie-details mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-700">
    These cookies enhance usability and personalization. They may remember user settings, improve navigation, and support optional features. Disabling these cookies may reduce convenience but will not impact core functionality.
  </p>

  <h3 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">2.3 Analytics Cookies (Optional)</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    These cookies help us understand how the platform is used so we can improve performance and reliability. They may collect aggregated usage metrics, navigation patterns, and performance diagnostics. All analytics data is anonymized or aggregated.
  </p>

  <h3 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">2.4 Third‑Party Cookies (Optional)</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    Some features rely on third-party services that set their own cookies, such as analytics providers, customer support tools, or embedded integrations. These providers maintain their own privacy and cookie practices.
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">3. How We Use Cookies</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    We use cookies to authenticate users, maintain secure sessions, protect the platform from fraud and abuse, measure performance, improve product design, and support customer service and operational insights. We do not use cookies to sell personal data or track users across unrelated websites.
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">4. Your Choices and Controls</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    You have full control over non‑essential cookies. You may accept or reject optional cookies at any time. Essential cookies remain active to ensure security and functionality. You may also manage cookies through your browser settings, including blocking, deleting, or restricting cookies. Disabling certain cookies may affect the performance or availability of some features.
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">5. Data Retention</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    Cookie retention periods vary based on purpose. Essential session cookies are deleted when you log out or close your browser. Functional cookies are typically retained for up to 12 months. Analytics cookies follow the retention policies of their respective providers. We do not retain cookie data longer than necessary for operational or compliance purposes.
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">6. Updates to This Policy</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    We may update this Cookie Policy to reflect changes in technology, regulation, or platform functionality. When updates occur, we will revise the “Last Updated” date below.
  </p>

  <h2 class="cookie-subtitle font-semibold mt-2 text-sm/6 text-gray-900">7. Contact Information</h2>
  <p class="text-sm/6 text-gray-700 mb-4">
    If you have questions about this Cookie Policy or our data practices, you may contact us at:
  </p>

  <p class="privacy-contact text-sm/6">
        <i class="text-sm/6">NTX Technologies <br>
        18383 Preston Rd, #202 <br>
        Dallas, TX 75252 <br>
        <%= mail_to "privacy@northtxtechnologies.com", "privacy@northtxtechnologies.com", class: "text-sky-500" %><br />
    </i></p>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 text-sm/6"><i><strong class="text-sm/6">Attention:</strong> Privacy & Compliance Team</i></p>
</div>
